info.longBusinessSummary: Electronic Arts Inc. develops, markets, publishes, and delivers games, content, and services for game consoles, PCs, and mobile phones worldwide. It develops and publishes games and services across various genres, such as sports, racing, first-person shooter, action, role-playing, and simulation; and live services offerings, including extra content and subscription offerings through its global football and American football franchises, such as EA SPORTS College Football and EA SPORTS Madden NFL, as well as based on its IP comprising The Sims, Apex Legends, and Battlefield. The company markets and sells its games and services through digital distribution and retail channels; and directly to mass market retailers, specialty stores, and distribution arrangements. Electronic Arts Inc. was incorporated in 1982 and is headquartered in Redwood City, California.

content.title: Electronic Arts Q1, Steve Madden Q2 miss, Harley-Davidson deal
content.description:
Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Allie Canal joins Market Domination with Josh Lipton to discuss some of the afternoon's trending tickers and stories.

Electronic Arts (EA) beat net booking estimates in its better-than-expected first quarter results.

Steve Madden (SHOO) missed estimates in its second quarter results and declined to provide full-year guidance.

Harley-Davidson (HOG) missed second quarter expectations, but the stock is trading higher after the company announced a partnership with KKR (KKR) and Pimco (PDI) to create $1.25 billion in discretionary cash.

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.
